  <p className="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-800">Minimal manicure bookings have grown 250% year-on-year across UK salons, with milky white finishes up 24%, according to <a href="https://theindustry.beauty/from-pastels-to-polka-dots-top-nail-trends-for-spring-summer-2026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fresha booking data published by TheIndustry.beauty</a>. The shift is not a seasonal softening — it is a structural change in what clients consider a desirable manicure. For nail technicians and salon owners, that distinction matters: a trend you wait out costs you differently to a category that is reshaping demand for the foreseeable future. Multiple forecasters now place sheer, clean, and barely-there finishes as a permanent fixture in the service mix, with maximalist trends running in parallel rather than replacing them.</p>
